Task 4 — Restaurant and Multiple Menu Items Injection
🎯 Objective
Demonstrate setter-based collection injection using AppConfig where a restaurant has multiple menu items.

🧱 Class-wise Design
1️. MenuItem Class

Attributes:

int itemId

String itemName

double price

Methods:

Setter methods for each.

A method showItem() to display item details.

2️. Restaurant Class

Attributes:

String restaurantName

List<MenuItem> menuItems

Methods:

Setter methods.

showMenu() to list all menu items.

3️. AppConfig Class

Responsibilities:

Marked with @Configuration.

Define beans for different MenuItems like Pizza, Burger, Pasta.

Create a Restaurant bean and inject the list of MenuItem beans using setter injection.

4️. Main Class

Responsibilities:

Load AppConfig using AnnotationConfigApplicationContext.

Retrieve the Restaurant bean.

Call showMenu().

📘 Expected Output
Restaurant: SpiceHub
Menu:
Item ID: 101, Name: Pizza, Price: 250.0
Item ID: 102, Name: Burger, Price: 150.0
Item ID: 103, Name: Pasta, Price: 200.0


